{"word":"ἐπήκοος","slug":"ἐπήκοος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπήκοος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐπακούω'><el>ἐπακούω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>listening</i> or <i>giving ear to</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>within hearing, within ear-shot</i>, <el>εἰς ἐπήκοον</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}